[{"id":"FT561946","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"Which of the following was the primary Ottoman response to the processes depicted in<u> Map 2 </u>?","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p><img alt=\"The figure presents a map titled &quot;Expansion of the Ottoman Empire, 1300 through 1683 &quot; The map shows portions of Africa at the bottom, Europe in the upper left hand corner, the Caspian Sea in the upper right hand corner, and the Arabian Peninsula and the Red Sea in the lower right hand corner. In the center the Mediterranean Sea, Constantinople, and the Black Sea are labeled from left to right and bottom to top. There is a legend labeled &quot;Territory Held,&quot; and the following four categories are given: 1. Ottoman territory in 1300. 2. Acquisitions from 1300 to 1451. 3. Acquisitions from 1451 to 1520. And 4. Acquisitions from 1520 to 1683  The shading for the category &quot;Ottoman territory in 1300° covers a small portion of northwestern Anatolia.  The shading for the category &quot;Acquisitions from 1300 to 1451° covers all of western, most of northern, and parts of central Anatolia and also includes most of southern and parts of central and eastern Greece, including the Peloponnese and a few small islands. The shading for the category &quot;Acquisitions from 1451 to 1520&quot; covers the Balkans, the remainder of Greece, the Crimean Peninsula and other territory to the east of the Black Sea, all of Anatolia, most of the western coast of the Arabian Peninsula, Syria, Lebanon, Palestine, Egypt, and part of northern Algeria. The shading for the category &quot;Acquisitions from 1520 to 1683° covers parts or all of Croatia, Hungary, Romania, and northern Bulgaria, most of Iraq, and territory along the western shores of the Persian Gulf, part of western Iran and the southern Caucasus, parts of the eastern coast of the Arabian Peninsula, the southwestern coast of the Arabian Peninsula, and the North African littoral from Libya to Tunisia and parts of Algeria.\" height=\"435\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/f8524d3a992815df0362a40ad3244257/original.jpg\" width=\"649\"></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<img alt=\"The figure presents a map titled \" height=\"434\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/4884f14e-87d6-47d8-9469-f66d548277ec.JPG\" width=\"649\">"}],"choicesHtml":["<p>Attempts to convert the empire’s non-Muslim population to Islam</p>","<p>Efforts to transform the empire into a parliamentary democracy</p>","<p>Attempts to reconcile Islamic law with Marxist ideals</p>","<p>Efforts to reform the government despite considerable internal opposition</p>"],"answer":2}]